1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:00,520
East.

2
00:00:00,570 --> 00:00:05,300
Too bad. I thought if you was heading north
I might be able to help you out.

3
00:00:05,350 --> 00:00:08,120
I m pushing myself late tonight.
I don t like to ride alone at night.

4
00:00:08,170 --> 00:00:12,470
I am one of those guys who gotta talk
or I fall asleep.

5
00:00:12,520 --> 00:00:15,000
My partner, he s got Lou to keep him company, but ...

6
00:00:15,050 --> 00:00:16,850
... I ain t got nobody at all.

7
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:19,290
- Where re you coming from?
- West.

8
00:00:19,340 --> 00:00:20,700
Yeah sure, I know, but ...

9
00:00:20,750 --> 00:00:22,130
... where? LA?

10
00:00:22,180 --> 00:00:24,590
- Maybe.
- I ve got a cousin out in LA ...

11
00:00:24,640 --> 00:00:27,840
- You don t say.
- Yeah. He s been out ...

12
00:00:27,890 --> 00:00:29,250
You're not much of a talker, are you?

13
00:00:29,300 --> 00:00:31,240
My mother taught me never to speak
to strangers.

14
00:00:31,290 --> 00:00:33,170
- Oh, wise guy is it.
- So what!?

15
00:00:33,220 --> 00:00:35,320
Okay, okay. Don t get sore.

16
00:00:35,370 --> 00:00:38,650
Trying to be sociable. That s all.

17
00:00:38,700 --> 00:00:40,350
Hey, Grandma!

18
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:44,440
Give me change for a dime, will you?.

19
00:00:51,610 --> 00:00:54,450
Let s have something quieter this time, Joe.
My head s splitting.

20
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:58,100
It that what's wrong with it?

21
00:00:59,000 --> 00:01:00,560
Done with your coffee?

22
00:01:00,610 --> 00:01:04,320
No.
And don t rush me, will you?

23
00:01:10,050 --> 00:01:11,930
Hey, turn that off.
Will you turn that thing off?

24
00:01:11,980 --> 00:01:13,800
- What s eating you now?
- Yeah, what s eating you?

25
00:01:13,850 --> 00:01:15,880
- That music, it stinks.
- Oh, you don t like it, huh?

26
00:01:15,930 --> 00:01:18,200
- No. Turn it off!
- Now wait a minute, pal.

27
00:01:18,250 --> 00:01:19,700
That was mine, that penny.

28
00:01:19,750 --> 00:01:24,440
This is a free country,
and I play whatever I want to.

29
00:01:24,490 --> 00:01:25,650
OK.

30
00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:27,850
Sure, and if you don t like it,
you don t have to listen to it.

31
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:29,750
And you can leave here any time, you want to.

32
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:31,450
OK OK. I m sorry I am.

33
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:33,850
First good piece played tonight,
and you don t like it.

34
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:38,210
Some people just ain t got any good taste.

35
00:01:47,370 --> 00:01:50,800
That tune...  That tune...

36
00:01:50,850 --> 00:01:53,250
Why was it always that rotten tune?

37
00:01:53,300 --> 00:01:58,440
Following me around, beating in my head,
never letting up.
